section.para:
			Annotate a document, read the layer, then produce a redacted copy in which
			only detected spans are replaced. Length is preserved: every character
			inside a mention becomes the mask character, and everything outside stays
			unchanged. PiiUsageExampleTest asserts the behavior shown
			here.

String text =
    "Contact jane@example.com, call (555) 123-4567, or charge card 4111 1111 1111 1111.";

Document document = new PiiAnnotator(new CursorPiiExtractor())
    .annotate(Document.of(text));

List<Annotation<PiiMention>> mentions = document.get(PiiAnnotator.PII);
// email, phone, card: exact spans, types, and normalized forms

String masked = Masker.mask(document, PiiAnnotator.PII, '*');
// "Contact ****************, call **************, or charge card *******************."
